the bad dream go away.

18:09.639 --> 18:11.422
<i> [eerie tone]</i>

18:18.565 --> 18:20.548
- harry?

18:20.650 --> 18:22.216
- He's working right now,
mommy.

18:22.318 --> 18:23.985
He told me he wants you
to take the pills.

18:24.070 --> 18:26.887
<i> [ominous music]</i>

18:26.990 --> 18:28.055
- harry?

18:28.158 --> 18:30.057
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

18:30.160 --> 18:32.610
harry? Harry?

18:34.497 --> 18:35.446
Harry!

18:37.917 --> 18:39.333
What is this?

18:39.419 --> 18:41.569
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

18:41.671 --> 18:44.789
what is this?

18:44.874 --> 18:45.456
- I have no idea.
Where did that come from?

18:45.542 --> 18:47.375
- From her.

18:47.460 --> 18:48.709
She gave it to me
with all these other pills.

18:48.795 --> 18:50.294
She wants to poison me!

18:50.380 --> 18:51.095
She wants to kill me and...

18:52.882 --> 18:55.883
Drink the baby's blood, harry.

18:55.969 --> 18:58.553
- I've seen this before.
It's postpartum.

18:58.638 --> 18:59.587
The hormones make new moms
go crazy.

18:59.689 --> 19:01.472
Sometimes they even
hurt the baby.

19:01.558 --> 19:02.390
She needs to be sedated again.

19:02.475 --> 19:04.308
- No!
No, I am not crazy!

19:04.394 --> 19:06.227
I'm not crazy!
I know what I saw.

19:06.312 --> 19:08.563
I know what I saw.

19:08.648 --> 19:09.730
Harry, look. Look at his leg.

19:09.816 --> 19:12.766
There are--
there are bite marks on the--

19:12.869 --> 19:14.652
look, look.
Look at the bite marks.

19:14.737 --> 19:16.103
There are bite marks.
There are bite--

19:16.206 --> 19:18.772
- that's just from
the little baby lojack

19:18.875 --> 19:19.940
that they put on the infants
in the hospital.

19:20.043 --> 19:20.992
This lazy nurse
totally scraped him

19:21.077 --> 19:21.993
when she took it off.

19:22.078 --> 19:23.494
I--[laughs]
I gave her hell,

19:23.580 --> 19:24.945
but I think it's gonna be fine.

19:25.048 --> 19:27.498
- Stop lying to me!

19:27.584 --> 19:29.133
- Yes, daddy.
Stop lying to her.

19:32.255 --> 19:34.622
I want her to take the pill
so she can be one of us.

19:34.724 --> 19:37.291
<i> [soft eerie music]</i>

19:37.393 --> 19:38.459
- one of us?

19:38.561 --> 19:39.460
What is she talking about,
harry?

19:39.562 --> 19:39.960
- She's just being cheeky.

19:40.063 --> 19:41.128
- I'm not.

19:41.231 --> 19:43.347
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

19:43.433 --> 19:44.765
if you take the pill,

19:44.851 --> 19:45.850
you become great
at whatever you're good at.

19:45.935 --> 19:47.852
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

19:47.937 --> 19:50.688
that's why daddy's
writing all those scripts.

19:50.773 --> 19:52.857
That's why I'm able to play
the paganini.

19:52.942 --> 19:56.277
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

19:56.362 --> 19:57.328
- is that true?

19:59.199 --> 20:01.115
Is that true?

20:01.201 --> 20:04.035
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

20:04.120 --> 20:04.835
- [scoffs]

20:06.122 --> 20:07.922
- [cries] harry.
- Take it, mommy.

20:09.792 --> 20:11.626
And we can be together forever.

20:11.711 --> 20:13.344
You won't mind
drinking the blood.

20:14.764 --> 20:15.296
It's not that bad.

20:17.934 --> 20:20.167
It feels so good
to be great at something.

20:20.270 --> 20:22.220
- It's a miracle, doris.

20:22.305 --> 20:24.222
Every one of your
designer dreams can come true.

20:24.307 --> 20:26.173
You'll be the best
in the world.

20:26.276 --> 20:26.691
- Stop it. Stop it!

20:28.111 --> 20:30.728
This is not for her.

20:30.813 --> 20:32.346
- You don't think
she's good enough, daddy?

20:32.448 --> 20:34.348
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

20:34.450 --> 20:35.566
- well, maybe if she
doesn't have the talent,

20:35.652 --> 20:36.484
she shouldn't take the risk.

20:39.672 --> 20:41.906
- Do you think
you're good enough, mommy?

20:42.008 --> 20:45.209
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

20:45.328 --> 20:47.545
<i> [music quickens]</i>

20:47.664 --> 20:54.669
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

21:09.102 --> 21:11.402
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

21:11.521 --> 21:12.737
- [gasps]
[baby cries]

21:12.855 --> 21:14.855
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

21:14.941 --> 21:15.606
- doris!

21:15.692 --> 21:17.608
[baby crying]

21:17.694 --> 21:20.278
- [panting]

21:20.363 --> 21:21.445
- [screeches]

21:21.531 --> 21:23.447
- [wails]

21:23.533 --> 21:25.082
- [groans]

21:28.288 --> 21:30.037
- [growls]

21:30.123 --> 21:31.589
[baby crying]
[growling]

21:32.542 --> 21:35.710
- [whimpers]

21:35.795 --> 21:37.878
- doris. Honey.

21:37.964 --> 21:39.213
- [crying]

21:39.299 --> 21:41.799
- come home with me.

21:41.884 --> 21:42.717
They can't hurt you
as long as you're with me.

21:42.802 --> 21:45.603
It's okay. It's okay.

21:45.722 --> 21:47.521
It's just me.

21:47.607 --> 21:50.274
<i> [somber music]</i>

21:50.393 --> 21:52.026
I'll explain everything.

21:52.111 --> 21:52.943
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

21:53.062 --> 21:55.446
come on. Come on.

21:55.565 --> 21:56.864
Come on.

21:56.949 --> 22:00.701
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

22:00.787 --> 22:02.486
let's go home.

22:04.741 --> 22:07.625
<i> [soft music]</i>

22:07.744 --> 22:14.749
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

22:25.161 --> 22:27.161
[seagulls calling]

22:45.848 --> 22:47.714
- you're not answering
your burner phone.

22:47.817 --> 22:48.715
<i> [eerie music]</i>

22:48.818 --> 22:50.651
you know how irritating
that is?

22:50.737 --> 22:52.319
- I'm sorry.

22:52.405 --> 22:54.321
I must have turned it off.

22:54.407 --> 22:55.889
- No worries.

22:55.992 --> 22:58.492
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

22:58.578 --> 22:59.827
you're lucky I ran into
speed racer,

22:59.912 --> 23:00.694
or I'd really be in a mood.

23:02.248 --> 23:04.665
You've been out here
painting a lot.

23:04.751 --> 23:06.066
- I guess so.

23:06.169 --> 23:07.535
- With nothing to show for it.

23:10.590 --> 23:11.422
You don't like them?
- About as much as I like

23:11.541 --> 23:13.740
the insect smudge
on my windshield.

23:13.843 --> 23:17.178
Actually,
I like the smudge more.

23:17.263 --> 23:18.712
At least something died
to put it there.

23:21.717 --> 23:24.769
On the subject
of small dead things...

23:24.887 --> 23:27.304
I need you
to run an errand for me.

23:29.942 --> 23:31.025
- [breathes heavily]

23:31.110 --> 23:32.860
what?

23:32.945 --> 23:35.196
- Oh, maybe you haven't heard,
but the gardeners

23:35.281 --> 23:36.197
just brought home
a little bundle of joy

23:36.282 --> 23:37.198
from the hospital.

23:37.283 --> 23:38.899
I want it.

23:39.535 --> 23:41.935
- Belle.

23:42.038 --> 23:43.103
Please, I--

23:43.206 --> 23:44.822
I can't.

23:46.793 --> 23:47.875
[hissing]

23:47.960 --> 23:50.161
- oh, yeah.

23:50.246 --> 23:51.495
Yeah, they've been here
the whole time.

23:51.581 --> 23:52.296
And not because they love art.

23:53.883 --> 23:56.250
They won't touch you
unless I get in a mood.

23:58.888 --> 23:59.587
- I won't do it.

24:01.591 --> 24:02.923
I'm not gonna help you
kill another baby.

24:04.927 --> 24:06.677
- Lordy, you mean I came

24:06.762 --> 24:08.629
all the way out here
for nothing?

24:08.731 --> 24:09.814
- Sorry.

24:10.766 --> 24:12.299
- Now I am in a mood.

24:12.401 --> 24:13.484
- [gasps]

24:16.239 --> 24:17.804
you can feed on anyone.

24:17.907 --> 24:19.573
On anybody.

24:19.659 --> 24:20.974
You don't need a baby.

24:21.077 --> 24:23.810
- Listen to me, monet.

24:23.913 --> 24:26.914
Newborn blood
is the elixir of the gods.

24:26.999 --> 24:28.315
It's pure.

24:28.417 --> 24:30.817
Untouched by a life
of booze and drugs.

24:30.920 --> 24:32.319
- [hisses]

24:32.421 --> 24:33.754
- the chemical swill
people call food.

24:33.840 --> 24:38.092
Newborn makes veal
taste like horseshit.

24:38.177 --> 24:39.660
And the longer we stand here,

24:39.762 --> 24:40.794
the less newborn it gets.

24:43.099 --> 24:44.548
So if you do nothing,

24:44.634 --> 24:48.552
just think about trying
to paint something

24:48.638 --> 24:50.221
with both of your eyes missing.

24:50.306 --> 24:54.308
<i> [tense music]</i>

24:54.393 --> 24:55.142
[chuckles]

24:55.228 --> 24:58.145
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:58.231 --> 25:01.065
- please.

25:01.150 --> 25:03.234
- [hisses]

25:03.319 --> 25:08.572
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:08.658 --> 25:10.124
- [gasps]

25:28.477 --> 25:31.378
<i> [somber music]</i>

25:31.480 --> 25:38.519
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:45.945 --> 25:48.996
[indistinct voices]

25:52.952 --> 25:55.869
<i> [suspenseful music]</i>

25:55.955 --> 26:03.010
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

26:35.828 --> 26:41.915
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

26:55.264 --> 26:57.264
[baby coos]

27:17.787 --> 27:20.788
[indistinct chatter, laughter]

27:25.628 --> 27:27.177
- so--but you want to be able
to change out the curtains

27:27.296 --> 27:28.629
from season to season,

27:28.714 --> 27:30.848
so the rod needs to be metal
but lighter.

27:30.966 --> 27:32.466
- I don't care.

27:32.551 --> 27:34.018
[laughs]

27:34.136 --> 27:36.186
no fucking way. No.

27:36.305 --> 27:37.971
If you're not gonna make him
an executive producer,

27:38.057 --> 27:40.641
then you gotta give him
a big, fat cut, okay?

27:42.361 --> 27:43.694
Okay, fine, go work on it.
I gotta go.

27:43.813 --> 27:45.279
- What was she thinking?

27:45.364 --> 27:46.947
Jesus.

27:47.033 --> 27:50.034
It's all so pedestrian
pottery barn hell.

27:50.152 --> 27:52.453
And, oh, my god.

27:52.538 --> 27:55.539
These rugs make me
want to puke.

27:55.658 --> 27:55.706
- Oh.

27:58.294 --> 28:01.361
- Um, I hope those scissors

28:01.464 --> 28:02.195
are for the curtains you put up
in the powder room.

28:02.298 --> 28:04.131
- Honey.

28:04.216 --> 28:05.632
You're awake.

28:05.718 --> 28:07.200
Why don't you go up
and feed the baby?

28:07.303 --> 28:08.836
Ursula will bring you
some soup.

28:10.389 --> 28:13.307
<i> [ominous music]</i>

28:13.392 --> 28:15.208
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:15.311 --> 28:16.427
- who is this?

28:18.814 --> 28:20.714
- He's a designer who does
lots of the houses around town.

28:20.816 --> 28:23.317
I asked him to come
help you finish the job.

28:23.402 --> 28:24.885
Anonymously.
- I don't need any help.

28:24.987 --> 28:26.720
- [muffled] no, of course
you don't, my dear.

28:26.822 --> 28:28.889
I've seen your--your boards,

28:28.991 --> 28:30.574
and there are some
lovely choices on there.

28:30.693 --> 28:32.242
Um...

28:32.361 --> 28:33.944
Not inspired, but lovely.

28:35.865 --> 28:38.165
[muffled]
so harry was telling us

28:38.250 --> 28:40.901
that you've been going through
a little, um,

28:41.003 --> 28:41.785
postpartum.

28:44.840 --> 28:46.507
- I don't want you
to lose this job, honey.

28:46.592 --> 28:48.208
I know how important it is
for your future.

28:49.261 --> 28:52.129
[baby cries]

28:53.432 --> 28:54.798
- ooh, ugh.

28:56.268 --> 28:59.353
- Oh, the sound of the crying
makes you do that.

28:59.438 --> 29:02.756
[baby crying]

29:02.858 --> 29:04.257
- go feed the baby.

29:04.360 --> 29:05.142
[muffled]
doris.

29:05.227 --> 29:08.261
<i> [unsettling music]</i>

29:08.364 --> 29:11.264
[baby crying]

29:11.367 --> 29:18.405
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:20.910 --> 29:23.961
[indistinct speech]

29:35.224 --> 29:42.262
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:45.901 --> 29:47.518
[banging on door]

29:49.655 --> 29:51.505
- you told belle where I was.

29:52.741 --> 29:53.824
- I didn't know
it was a secret.

29:53.909 --> 29:55.476
- [coughs]

29:55.578 --> 29:56.527
- you know, it's pretty hard
to stay out of your life

29:56.612 --> 29:57.611
when you start showing up
at my door.

29:57.696 --> 29:59.446
- Do you know
what she wants from me?

29:59.532 --> 30:00.447
- She didn't say.

30:00.533 --> 30:01.782
- The gardeners
have a new baby.

30:01.867 --> 30:03.567
She wants me to steal it
for her.

30:03.669 --> 30:05.786
- It's her weakness.
- If I don't do it,

30:05.871 --> 30:07.237
she said
she'll tear out my eyes.

30:07.339 --> 30:08.622
- You know, so do it.

30:08.707 --> 30:11.208
- I can't!
Not ever again!

30:12.211 --> 30:13.961
I'm scared, mickey.

30:14.046 --> 30:15.629
- Do you want
to be safe from belle?

30:15.714 --> 30:18.265
Right?
From everything and everyone?

30:20.553 --> 30:22.102
The answer's right here.
- Ugh!

30:23.022 --> 30:24.421
- The fuck is wrong with you?

30:24.523 --> 30:26.223
- What the fuck
is wrong with you?

30:28.394 --> 30:30.527
I want to make things right.

30:30.613 --> 30:34.364
For all the times
I did what belle wanted.

30:34.450 --> 30:35.566
I want to go after
the gardener baby.

30:37.570 --> 30:38.952
- Go after it?
- To save it.

30:40.906 --> 30:42.322
If I don't bring her the baby,

30:42.408 --> 30:43.440
she's just gonna get
someone else to do it.

30:43.542 --> 30:44.825
Or she's gonna take it herself.

30:44.910 --> 30:47.160
I need to make sure
she never gets her hands on it.

30:47.246 --> 30:48.612
- What are you gonna do
with a baby, huh?

30:48.714 --> 30:50.130
Have you thought about that?

30:51.083 --> 30:52.332
- Take care of it.

30:52.418 --> 30:54.501
Raise it.

30:54.587 --> 30:56.086
I'm serious, mickey.

30:56.755 --> 30:58.288
I'm gonna get clean.

30:58.390 --> 31:01.091
I'm gonna make a fresh start.

31:01.176 --> 31:02.509
And being responsible
for a baby

31:02.595 --> 31:05.012
will make me be responsible
for myself.

31:05.097 --> 31:07.014
- Yeah, I'm pretty sure it
doesn't work that way, karen.

31:07.099 --> 31:08.732
- I need your help.

31:10.686 --> 31:11.852
I can't do it alone.

31:11.937 --> 31:13.020
I'm afraid I'm gonna
screw it up.

31:13.105 --> 31:14.071
Look, my hands are shaking.

31:15.441 --> 31:16.356
- Why should I help you?

31:16.442 --> 31:18.242
- Because...

31:20.446 --> 31:21.828
Because if you love me,
you'll help me.

31:25.784 --> 31:27.117
And because you need to.

31:27.202 --> 31:29.369
- Oh, I "need" to?
- Yeah.

31:29.455 --> 31:30.370
You need to.
You need to do something good.

31:30.456 --> 31:32.989
<i> [emotional music]</i>

31:33.092 --> 31:34.824
you need to remember
what that feels like

31:34.927 --> 31:36.093
before it's too late.

31:38.881 --> 31:41.632
Mickey...

31:41.717 --> 31:44.434
Do this with me, please.

31:45.804 --> 31:46.637
Please.

31:46.722 --> 31:49.222
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:49.308 --> 31:50.641
[breath shakes]
please, mickey.

31:50.726 --> 31:57.781
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:13.165 --> 32:15.882
[baby fussing]

32:16.001 --> 32:22.005
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:38.440 --> 32:39.856
- what are we gonna name him?

32:43.779 --> 32:45.028
- I like eli.

32:46.198 --> 32:47.531
Eli?

32:49.118 --> 32:51.168
- I like eli too.

32:55.708 --> 32:56.673
- You hurt him...

32:59.128 --> 33:01.044
When you did
what you did to him.

33:05.050 --> 33:06.049
I know it wasn't a dream.

33:09.388 --> 33:12.055
- Baby blood works better
than older person blood.

33:13.726 --> 33:16.443
I make myself cry
when I play on baby blood

33:16.562 --> 33:18.445
because it sounds so beautiful.

33:18.564 --> 33:19.863
- [exhales deeply]

33:19.948 --> 33:22.866
<i> [soft eerie music]</i>

33:22.951 --> 33:27.871
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:27.956 --> 33:29.322
he's your brother, alma.

33:35.080 --> 33:36.747
Alma, you can't do that to him.

33:38.634 --> 33:41.835
You can't do that to any baby.

33:44.089 --> 33:44.588
- I'm sorry.

33:46.759 --> 33:48.759
I won't do it again, I promise.

33:54.767 --> 33:57.734
I don't want
to lose our family.

33:57.820 --> 33:59.820
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:59.938 --> 34:02.022
- I'm scared
that it's already lost.

34:07.279 --> 34:09.646
[crying]

34:09.748 --> 34:12.082
- not if you become
like daddy and I.

34:12.167 --> 34:16.086
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:16.171 --> 34:18.088
I don't think daddy thinks
you're good enough.

34:18.173 --> 34:20.657
That's why he doesn't want you
to take the pill.

34:20.759 --> 34:22.826
He thinks you'll become
a pale person.

34:22.928 --> 34:26.430
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:26.515 --> 34:28.164
but I believe in you, mommy.

34:28.267 --> 34:33.670
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:33.772 --> 34:34.554
- you do?

34:38.143 --> 34:39.943
I just can't believe that
your father would do this,

34:40.028 --> 34:41.445
that he would bring
all this darkness and horror

34:41.530 --> 34:43.063
into our family.

34:46.452 --> 34:48.485
- But it's not darkness.

34:49.872 --> 34:50.904
It's a beauty and light.

34:54.543 --> 34:56.493
Don't you hear it when I play?

34:57.963 --> 35:00.029
Think about all those people

35:00.132 --> 35:03.366
that are gonna be touched
by daddy's work.

35:03.469 --> 35:06.169
Think of those beautiful rooms
you can design.

35:08.307 --> 35:10.874
Being a little less afraid
of the blood.

35:10.976 --> 35:13.927
Being more afraid
of being mediocre.

35:14.012 --> 35:18.381
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:18.484 --> 35:19.215
you can have it all, mommy.

35:19.318 --> 35:22.936
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:23.021 --> 35:24.571
just like us.

35:31.997 --> 35:35.365
- It's not okay
to hurt people...

35:35.450 --> 35:37.450
Just to be good at something.

35:37.536 --> 35:43.590
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:47.379 --> 35:51.798
<i> [tense music]</i>

35:51.884 --> 35:53.583
- you get used to the blood.

35:53.685 --> 35:56.252
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:56.355 --> 35:58.221
forget where it came from.

36:01.193 --> 36:02.642
But that feeling
when you go to work

36:02.728 --> 36:04.978
and that perfection
just pours out of you--

36:05.063 --> 36:06.730
you never get used to that.

36:08.567 --> 36:09.566
It's so wonderful, mommy.

36:12.905 --> 36:14.204
I want it for you.

36:18.160 --> 36:19.409
I love you so much.

36:19.494 --> 36:26.550
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:36.511 --> 36:37.427
open.

36:37.512 --> 36:40.647
<i> [dark music]</i>

36:40.766 --> 36:46.820
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:55.697 --> 37:01.868
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:01.954 --> 37:03.169
- [laughs]

